<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_03bbaa44-56c6-48ec-a42e-4ebbfc6ec768" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>9.2.7</sptc><title id="_baed7d2b-bf47-4127-b7da-7fc8dfb85e92">Protection of Class 1 buildings—separation of Class 10a buildings on an allotment</title><archive-num>2019: Figure 3.7.2.6</archive-num><subclause id="_439be980-9e07-4a26-80ac-db4d8064f1c4" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_f79ea70d-1dae-435b-aedf-cfa6381d39a6">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>The following methods are acceptable for the protection of a Class 1 building where two or more Class 10a buildings on the same allotment are located between and are associated with different Class 1 buildings:</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_74b3113b-2a46-47c1-b947-b243ceaddd9e">Each Class 10a building must be separated from each other by a distance of not less than 1.8 m, as shown in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/766_0.6.0.xml#_334a024b-e5ce-43eb-aa73-bc584ecc9c99" id="_95e647ac-94a4-4fec-acd7-5c40bb5f6fe9" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.7a</xref>.</li><li id="_28e839f9-8bb2-438c-b0b5-9c610780db2f">Each Class 10a building must be separated from each other by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_71a35882-8dfd-4e52-b3d4-5e5fb218ad06" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external walls</xref> complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1848_1.9.0.xml#_263a5890-898c-4938-a6e8-4bd931480b0f" id="_b7c013f5-5980-4362-a779-d38fb2616703" scope="local" type="clause">9.2.3</xref>, as shown in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/767_0.6.0.xml#_8a328573-8517-4299-a13d-c751ef4e6827" id="_ebd4a9ec-c4f1-4738-82c1-afb1d0ca3bc1" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.7b</xref>.</li><li id="_49f27f69-6701-44f3-ac47-2c823f9b715a">Each Class 10a building must be separated from each Class 1 building by a distance of not less than 900 mm, as shown in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/769_0.7.0.xml#_8b1256c8-1a30-4f76-becb-ed73d29b80d4" id="_2e580fce-6ac8-4721-98cf-639d37d0f592" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.7c</xref>.</li><li id="_97a9eefc-e9c4-49a6-a6ee-0ac7a247b9ca">Each Class 10a building must be separated from each Class 1 building by <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1267_2.3.0.xml#_d87c7cc0-d0b0-40ab-9a5b-d070ed6e115e" id="_0d3ea85f-311c-452d-a844-4d7918c814cc" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">external walls</xref> complying with <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1848_1.9.0.xml#_263a5890-898c-4938-a6e8-4bd931480b0f" id="_48986095-8051-4a85-9b3f-66905162af0f" scope="local" type="clause">9.2.3</xref>, as shown in <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/770_0.6.0.xml#_75afe945-d95d-4d8b-80b5-3559954479c5" id="_0a0b3db7-6ee1-43f8-bdba-7d6bd6d59d30" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="image-reference">Figure 9.2.7d</xref>.</li><li id="_b21b6308-a887-4a1e-9899-5d0e2eceb32a">Each Class 10a building must be separated by a wall complying with <xref format="dita" href="/t